    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your kind favors &amp; <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bidb.xml#bi0071">the book of the feuds
                            of the isles</title>
                    </bibl> demand my gratefull thanks. everything else
                    you mention will be welcome: <persName ref="pe0040">Ld
                        Buchan</persName> need not be troubled ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    <rs type="art" ref="ar0111">his drawings</rs> for I have all that <unclear reason="illegible">
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0651">Iona</placeName>
                    </unclear> can afford his notes &amp; inscriptions will be
                    most acceptable. But do not fatigue yrself ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> that
                    or anything else. the parcel is gone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful &amp; affect
                        H. Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho.
                    Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0699">London</placeName> April 1.
                    1773.</dateline>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
